==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Apish
<hw>Ap"ish</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the qualities
of an ape; prone to imitate in a servile manner. Hence: Apelike;
fantastically silly; foppish; affected; trifling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>apish</qex> gallantry of a fantastic boy.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apishly</ent>⟦br⟧
